## 🎯 Goal
Implement a proper SMS OTP service integration in the backend to replace the current stub implementation in `backend/utils/otpService.js`.

## 📝 Current Implementation
Currently, the SMS OTP service is just a stub that logs to console:
```javascript
exports.sendOtpPhone = async (phone, otp) => {
    console.log(`Sending OTP ${otp} to phone ${phone}`);
    // integrate actual SMS service here
};

Proposed Changes
Integrate a proper SMS service provider (e.g., Twilio, MessageBird, or AWS SNS)
Implement proper error handling and validation
Add rate limiting for OTP requests
Add logging for successful/failed OTP deliveries
Add environment variables for SMS service configuration
